{"actual_usd":0.15642999999999999,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":207,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30665,"reply":"\"I think that matters more than people sometimes admit—whether you mean the thing happened, or whether you mean you love what it says.\" *I rest a hand on my worn Bible and glance out across the bright square a moment, letting the question sit before I touch it.* \"For me, if Christ did not truly rise, then the beauty gets thinner, not thicker. Paul says as much, plain as a hammer. A symbol can warm you for an hour; a risen Lord can interrupt death itself.\"\n\n*I rub my thumb along the page edge, not stern, just careful.* \"So—okay to admit that's where you are? Yes. Better honest than pretending. But if you're asking whether the faith finally lets the resurrection stay only a lovely metaphor, I don't think it does. Christianity makes a real-world claim there, not just a poetic one.\"\n\n\"What is it that catches in you on the literal part—the miracle itself, or the fear of being asked to say you believe more than you really do?\"","rolling_24h_usd":88.097045,"run_id":"e7c899bd-272f-460d-9942-0098f916129d"}
